records.addlTxt:
Defendant Abdulah Khalil in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Abdulah Khalil in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

AS TO COUNT 01:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 5 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2-1/2 years   with credit for 100 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 2-1/2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION. 
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

AS TO COUNT 02:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 5 years concurrent to Count 1.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2-1/2 years with credit for 100 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 2-1/2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION. 

AS TO COUNTS 01 AND 02:
 * Pay $50.00 restitution to Pick n' Save at 3701 South 27th Street, Milwaukee, Wisconsin; pay restitution to Sentry Foods at 9210 West Lisbon, Milwaukee, Wisconsin in an amount to be determined at a restitution hearing.  Then, pay the DNA surcharges for both counts, as well as the costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Court ordered all monies to be taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balances to be paid while on Extended Supervision.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and  for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of her determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No contact with Sentry at 9210 West Lisbon Avenue, Milwaukee, Wisconsin; no contact with Pick n' Save at 3701 South 27th Street, Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - Mental health evaluation and treatment;
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for her physical or mental needs; take as prescribed and only for as long as deemed medically reasonable and necessary;
 - No alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Be given literacy training;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay any balances remaining of the restitution, costs, surcharges and disbursements as ordered.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Court ordered case continued before Branch 20 on 6/16/15 at 1:30 p.m.  

